'''亞美尼亞高原'''（Armenian Highlands，{{lang-hy|Հայկական լեռնաշխարհ|Haykakan leṙnašxarh}}，英文名稱另有Armenian Upland，  Armenian plateau，或是Armenian tableland，<ref name="Hewsen">[[Robert_Hewsen|Hewsen, Robert H.]] "The Geography of Armenia" in ''The Armenian People From Ancient to Modern Times Volume I: The Dynastic Periods: From Antiquity to the Fourteenth Century''. [[Richard_G._Hovannisian|Richard G. Hovannisian]] (ed.) New York: St. Martin's Press, 1997, pp. 1-17</ref>）是組成[[西亞|西亞]]北部的三個[[高原|高原]]中，位居中央，高度最高的一座。<ref name="Hewsen" />亞美尼亞高原從西方，順著時鐘方向，受[[安纳托利亞|安纳托利亞高原]]、[[高加索|高加索]]、[[庫拉-阿拉斯低地|庫拉-阿拉斯低地]]、[[伊朗高原|伊朗高原]]、[[美索不達米亞|美索不達米亞]]所包圍。亞美尼亞高原受到[[亞拉拉特平原|亞拉拉特平原]]（其中有[[亞拉拉特山|亞拉拉特山]]）所分隔，而分成東西兩個區域。所謂[[西亞美尼亞|西亞美尼亞]]就是今日所稱的[[東部安那托利亞地區|東部安那托利亞地區]]，而所謂的{{le|東亞美尼亞|Eastern Armenia}}即為今日的[[小高加索山脈|小高加索山脈]]，也稱Caucasus Minor，或是古代所稱的Anti-Caucasus，<ref>{{Cite EB1911|wstitle=Caucasia|volume=5|page=547}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|last=Reclus|first=Onésime|url=https://archive.org/details/abirdseyeviewwo00clargoog|title=A Bird's-eye View of the World|date=1892|publisher=Ticknor|page=[https://archive.org/details/abirdseyeviewwo00clargoog/page/n288 264]|language=en|quote=anti caucasus.}}</ref>即“在高加索對面”的意思。

在[[鐵器時代|鐵器時代]]，這個地區以[[烏拉爾圖|烏拉爾圖]]（或其他類似稱呼-Urartu、Uruatri、Urashtu）的名字而為人知。後來它被稱為“大亞美尼亞”，是[[亞美尼亞歷史|亞美尼亞歷史]]的中心地區，另外三個與[[亞美尼亞人|亞美尼亞人]]有關的[[地緣政治學|地緣政治學]]地區是[[小亞美尼亞|小亞美尼亞]]、{{link-en|索芬|Sophene}}、和[[科馬基尼王國|科馬基尼]]。<ref>{{cite book|last=Adalian|first=Rouben Paul|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=QS-vSjHObOYC|title=Historical dictionary of Armenia|publisher=Scarecrow Press|year=2010|isbn=978-0810874503|edition=2nd|location=Lanham, MD|pages=336–8|access-date=2020-02-07|archive-date=2017-10-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171019233056/https://books.google.com/books?id=QS-vSjHObOYC|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last=Grierson|first=Otto Mørkholm; edited by Philip|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=U_5Ez0kAOuIC|title=Early Hellenistic coinage : from the accession of Alexander to the Peace of Apamea (336-188 B.C.)|author2=Westermark, Ulla|publisher=Cambridge University Press|year=1991|isbn=0521395046|edition=Repr.|location=Cambridge|page=175|access-date=2020-02-07|archive-date=2020-03-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317182336/https://books.google.com/books?id=U_5Ez0kAOuIC|dead-url=no}}</ref>

歷史學家假設，亞美尼亞人的名稱在歷史紀錄上出現之前，這個區域曾有幾個不同的族裔存在，這些族裔在亞美尼亞語通行後而統一。<ref name="La Porta 2018">{{cite encyclopaedia|last=La Porta|first=Sergio|year=2018|editor-last=Nicholson|editor-first=Oliver|chapter=Armenia|title=[[牛津古典时代晚期词典|The Oxford Dictionary of Late Antiquity]]|quote=Among the diversity of ethnicities residing on the Armenian plateau in Antiquity, the Armenian-speakers came to prominence during the Achaemenid period.|publisher=Cambridge University Press|location=Cambridge|chapter-url=https://www.oxfordreference.com/view/10.1093/acref/9780198662778.001.0001/acref-9780198662778-e-439?rskey=LhAqa2&result=1|access-date=2021-06-05|archive-date=2021-06-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210606053828/https://www.oxfordreference.com/view/10.1093/acref/9780198662778.001.0001/acref-9780198662778-e-439?rskey=LhAqa2&result=1}}</ref>在過去6,000多年來，亞美尼亞高原的人口似乎維持高度的區域性遺傳。<ref name=":5">{{Cite journal|last1=Hovhannisyan|first1=Anahit|last2=Jones|first2=Eppie|last3=Delser|first3=Pierpaolo Maisano|last4=Schraiber|first4=Joshua|last5=Hakobyan|first5=Anna|last6=Margaryan|first6=Ashot|last7=Hrechdakian|first7=Peter|last8=Sahakyan|first8=Hovhannes|last9=Saag|first9=Lehti|last10=Khachatryan|first10=Zaruhi|last11=Yepiskoposyan|first11=Levon|date=2020-06-24|title=AN ADMIXTURE SIGNAL IN ARMENIANS AROUND THE END OF THE BRONZE AGE REVEALS WIDESPREAD POPULATION MOVEMENT ACROSS THE MIDDLE EAST|url=https://www.biorxiv.org/content/10.1101/2020.06.24.168781v1|journal=bioRxiv|language=en|pages=2020.06.24.168781|doi=10.1101/2020.06.24.168781|s2cid=220253091|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200815015551/https://www.biorxiv.org/content/10.1101/2020.06.24.168781v1.full|archive-date=2020-08-15|quote=We show that Armenians have indeed remained unadmixed through the Neolithic and at least until the first part of the Bronze Age, and fail to find any support for historical suggestions by Herodotus of an input from the Balkans. However, we do detect a genetic input of Sardinian-like ancestry during or just after the Middle-Late Bronze Age. A similar input at approximately the same time was detected in East Africa, suggesting large-scale movement both North and South of the Middle East. Whether such large-scale population movement was a result of climatic or cultural changes is unclear, as well as the true source of gene flow remains an open question that needs to be addressed in future ancient DNA studies. [...] We focused on solving a long-standing puzzle regarding Armenians’ genetic roots. Although the Balkan hypothesis has long been considered the most plausible narrative on the origin of Armenians, our results strongly reject it, showing that modern Armenians are genetically distinct from both the ancient and present-day populations from the Balkans. On the contrary, we confirmed the pattern of genetic affinity between the modern and ancient inhabitants of the Armenian Highland since the Chalcolithic, which was initially identified in previous studies. [...] Sardinians have the highest affinity to early European farmers [...]|access-date=2021-06-05|dead-url=no}}</ref>最近的研究顯示，亞美尼亞人是亞美尼亞高原的[[原住民|原住民]]，長期在這個地區形成一個獨特的{{le|遺傳隔離|Genetic isolate}}群。<ref name=":422">{{Cite journal|last1=Haber|first1=Marc|last2=Mezzavilla|first2=Massimo|last3=Xue|first3=Yali|last4=Comas|first4=David|last5=Gasparini|first5=Paolo|last6=Zalloua|first6=Pierre|last7=Tyler-Smith|first7=Chris|date=21 October 2015|title=Genetic evidence for an origin of the Armenians from Bronze Age mixing of multiple populations|journal=European Journal of Human Genetics|volume=24|issue=6|pages=931–936|doi=10.1038/ejhg.2015.206|pmid=26486470|pmc=4820045|quote=Our tests suggest that Armenians had no significant mixture with other populations in their recent history and have thus been genetically isolated since the end of the Bronze Age, 3000 years ago.|doi-access=free}}</ref>這個地區在[[古典時代|古典時代]]也有[[亞述人|亞述人]]、[[喬治亞人|喬治亞人]]、[[希臘人|希臘人]]、[[猶太人|猶太人]]、和[[伊朗人|伊朗人]]等少數民族居住。在[[中世紀|中世紀]]，[[阿拉伯人|阿拉伯人]]，以及特別是[[土庫曼人|土庫曼人]]和[[庫爾德人|庫爾德人]]大量移入亞美尼亞高原定居。這個地區西半部的基督徒在1915年[[亞美尼亞種族滅絕|亞美尼亞種族滅絕]]時期受到[[種族滅絕|滅絕]]。今天，這個地區東半部主要是居住著亞美尼亞人、[[亞塞拜然族|亞塞拜然人]]、和喬治亞亞人。而西半部主要是居住庫爾德人（包括[[雅茲迪|雅茲迪]]人）、土耳其人、亞塞拜然人、亞美尼亞人（包括{{le|隱性亞美尼亞人|Hidden Armenians}}和[[赫姆辛人|赫姆辛人]]）、和[[扎扎人|扎扎人]]。

在大部分的已知歷史上，這個地區是由{{le|亞美尼亞貴族|Armenian nobility}}和國家治理，這些治理階級或是獨立的亞美尼亞國的一部分、或是[[附庸|附庸]]、或是外國統治者的一部分。東亞美尼亞的大部分地區從16世紀開始受伊朗[[薩法維王朝|薩法維王朝]]統治，在1828年被[[俄羅斯帝國|俄羅斯帝國]]併吞，再成為[[蘇聯|蘇聯]]的一部分，而[[西亞美尼亞|西亞美尼亞]]的大部分地區則由[[鄂圖曼帝國|鄂圖曼帝國]]統治，後來併入[[土耳其|土耳其]]。今日，這個高原地區分屬土耳其、喬治亞、亞美尼亞、亞塞拜然、和伊朗五個國家。

